data.name: lblLNotes.Text
data.value:
-"Download To Device" saves new changes until power cycling the device.
-Com ports parameters will not be saved to file and will be modified inside Com Ports tab. not by the below buttons.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value:
Acquiring DeadLoad: 1.Unload the Load cell or put load that you want to be as the dead load point. 2.Write the Current load in the weight Low text box. 3.Press "Acquire DeadLoad". "Wait..." will be displayed for above 4 seconds then the dead load is calibrated and displayed.
Acquiring Span: 1.Put the load that you want to calibrate with. 2.Write the load value in the weight High text box. 3.Press "Acquire Span". "Wait..." wil be displayed for above 4 seconds then the span load is calibrated and displayed.
"Save" -Press to save calibration date in permanent memory. otherwise data will lose when powering off the device.

data.name: lblVnotes.Text
data.value:
-Press "Find Device/s". the GUI will search and display all the connected devices.from this point the data in the other tabs will not be available.to exit View All mode press "Stop View All"button (switched from "Find Device/s.
-The communication settings(Baud Rate . Parity....)of all the connected devices must be identical.
-It must be different address for each connected device.
-Writing to log File will be delayed if activating "View All".
